 ## 11. Direct quotes (for positioning)
 
+### 14. Competitive cross-reference
+
+See [`docs/features/research-scout-landscape.md`](./research-scout-landscape.md) for the broader competitive set (Elicit, Research Rabbit, Feedly Leo, Emergent Mind, Perplexity, Arc Search, etc.).
+
+**TL;DR of where Yutori sits in that landscape**: It's the **only general-purpose agentic scout platform** with browser automation and live artifacts (vs. academic-only Elicit, graph-only Research Rabbit, arxiv-only Emergent Mind, RSS-only Feedly Leo, mobile-only Arc Search). Thedi differentiates by being **deeper in one vertical** (research digest) with a **critique pipeline**, not a general monitoring platform.
+
+**Direct Competitor Comparison:** See Section 14.1 for a detailed feature comparison table across Yutori, Thedi, and key competitors (Elicit, Feedly Leo, Arc Search, Perplexity).
+
+### 14.1 Direct Competitor Comparison Table
+
+| Feature | Yutori | Thedi | Competitor A (Elicit) | Competitor B (Feedly Leo) | Competitor C (Arc Search) |
+|---|---|---|---|---|---|
+| **Primary Use Case** | General web monitoring (news, deals, research) | Research digest (academic + tech) | Academic literature review | RSS feed curation + AI summaries | Mobile-first web browsing |
+| **Agent Architecture** | Single-agent per scout | Multi-agent loop (selector → critic → refiner) | Single-agent RAG | Single-agent summarization | Single-agent search |
+| **Audit Trail** | User-visible (pages visited, reasoning) | Thedi has `audit_log` but not user-visible | No audit trail | No audit trail | No audit trail |
+| **Delivery Channels** | Email, iOS, Slack, Webhooks, Web | Email, Web | Email, Web | Email, RSS, Web | Mobile app only |
+| **Personalization** | Per-scout prompt only | Cross-scout learning + critic loop | Per-query only | Per-feed only | Per-user search history |
+| **Live Artifacts** | Yes (shareable HTML dashboards) | No | No | No | No |
+| **Team Collaboration** | View/subscribe only (no editing) | No | No | No | No |
+| **Pricing Model** | Per-run usage | TBD | Free + Pro subscription | Free + Pro subscription | Free |
+| **MCP Support** | Yes (Design Ecosystem) | No | No | No | No |
+| **Browser Automation** | Yes (cloud-based) | No | No | No | No |
+| **Local Execution** | Yes (Yutori Local tier) | No | No | No | No |
+
+**Key Takeaway:** Yutori is the only general-purpose agentic scout platform with browser automation and live artifacts. Thedi differentiates by being deeper in research with a critique pipeline. Elicit and Feedly Leo are more mature in their verticals but lack agent autonomy. Arc Search is mobile-only and doesn't support persistent monitoring.
+
+### 14.2 Competitor Deep Dives
+
+**Elicit (elicit.com)**
+- **Focus:** Academic literature review and research synthesis
+- **Strengths:** Large paper database, citation graph, structured extraction
+- **Weaknesses:** No web monitoring, no browser automation, no persistent scouts
+- **Thedi Position:** Thedi can match Elicit's research depth while adding persistent monitoring (Yutori's strength)
+
+**Feedly Leo (feedly.com/leo)**
+- **Focus:** RSS feed curation with AI summarization
+- **Strengths:** Mature RSS infrastructure, team sharing, integrations
+- **Weaknesses:** No web monitoring beyond RSS, no browser automation, single-agent
+- **Thedi Position:** Thedi can match Feedly's feed curation while adding web monitoring and multi-agent critique
+
+**Arc Search (arcsearch.app)**
+- **Focus:** Mobile-first AI web browsing
+- **Strengths:** Excellent mobile UX, fast search, clean summaries
+- **Weaknesses:** No persistent monitoring, no browser automation, no team features
+- **Thedi Position:** Thedi can match Arc's UX while adding persistent monitoring and team collaboration
+
+**Perplexity (perplexity.ai)**
+- **Focus:** AI-powered search engine
+- **Strengths:** Real-time web search, citation tracking, Pro features
+- **Weaknesses:** No persistent monitoring, no browser automation, no team features
+- **Thedi Position:** Thedi can match Perplexity's search while adding persistent monitoring and multi-agent critique
+
+**Note:** The doc currently references `docs/features/research-scout-landscape.md` for broader competitive set. This section should be updated to include the above competitors with specific feature comparisons.
